# [NVIDIA Studio Driver R610 (610.47) | Windows 11](https://www.nvidia.com/en-us/drivers/details/271420/)

NVIDIA Studio Drivers provide artists, creators, and 3D developers the best performance and reliability when working with creative applications. To achieve the highest level of reliability, Studio Drivers undergo extensive testing against multi-app creator workflows and multiple revisions of the top creative applications from Adobe to Autodesk and beyond.  

**Applications**  

The May NVIDIA Studio Driver provides optimal support for the latest new creative applications and updates including performance optimized releases for ComfyUI and Llama.cpp.  

**Fixed Application Bugs**  

- Adobe: NVIDIA Driver crash in Lightroom Classic [6090770]
- Autodesk Forma: OpenGL driver memory leak during camera orbit [5935127]
- Foundry Mari 7.0v2 viewport displays flickering [6102981]
- Like a Dragon: Infinite Wealth: Shadow/light flicker after driver update [5973185]
- Enshrouded: Missing terrain after driver update [5955501]
- Visual corruption may appear in certain games using Godot engine [5955501]

**Fixed General Bugs**  

- Apple Studio Display XDR only displays 480p after driver update [5976295]
- Samsung The Frame: Using display's Game mode disables key functionality [5825631]
- Multimonitor gaming stability improvements when using V-SYNC [5343252]
- Enhanced smoothness when DLSS Frame Generation is used with V-SYNC [5999586]

---

## Overview

This package installs the latest Nvidia Studio Driver (aka the creator ready driver) for Windows 10/11 with the default settings. 
**This driver is meant for Nvidia GeForce GTX 1xxx series and GeForce RTX series (20xx and newer) cards, it also works with most Nvidia RTX / RTX PRO / Quadro cards.**
You can automate driver updates with `choco upgrade nvidia-studio-driver -y` in a scheduled task.
You can revert to previous driver versions with `choco install` and specifying the version. i.e. `choco install nvidia-studio-driver --version=581.29 -yf`

## Package Parameters

The following package parameters can be set to customize the installation.

  - `/SkipCompatCheck` - Skip the compatibility check that ensures your GPU is supported by this driver version. Use at your own risk.
  - `/RemoveOtherVersions` - If desired, remove other versions of the NVIDIA display driver from windows after install.
    - Can trigger an unexpected reboot (uncommon)
    - Removes any nvidia display driver that doesn't match the version of the newly installed version, only affects display driver other components are untouched.
    - Can help prevent windows from reverting to a 'newer' driver on reboot if reverting to an older version of the driver.

Example param usage with choco install command:
`choco install nvidia-studio-driver --params "'/RemoveOtherVersions'"`
